Package rpc.datagen

Class Summary
CausalModelGenerator The Causal Model Generator generates a random causal model over the current schema with a pre-specified number of dependencies to add.
Connector Connector abstract class defines core methods needed to create links (i.e., relationships or connections) between entities.
ConstantConnector The Constant Connector class creates a constant number of relationships for each given entity.
CPTConnector A CPTConnector will generate a list of entity IDs.
CPTParent CPTParent is a conditional probability table consisting of a set of discrete probability distribution for different combinations of parent values.
CPTPrior CPTPrior is a conditional probability table consisting of a single discrete probability distribution.
DataGenerator Data Generator provides methods for instantiating a relational database based on a generative causal model and its parameterization.
Parameterization Parameterization of a causal model structure.
PoissonConnector The Poisson Connector class creates a number of relationships drawn from a Poisson distribution.
VertexData Vertex data contains the necessary information in order to generate the variable (attribute or structure) for which the vertex corresponds to in the causal model.
